%S A397864 3,63,99,323,5183,777923,837539,1327103,6718463,12446783,16402499,
%T A397864 17948739,229159043,432972863,741663683
%N A397864 Numbers k such that there are more divisors d of k where d + n/d is a square than those where it is not.
%C A397864 Rephrased: Numbers k such that 2*A211996(k) > tau(k).
%C A397864 Most of the terms are a product of twin primes that add up to a square (A232878). Since the product of such twin primes is (18*n^2)^2-1 all 4 pairs sum to square.
%e A397864 99 has 6 pairs; (1, 99), (3, 33), (9, 11), (11, 9), (33, 3), (99, 1). 4 of them sum to a square. Therefore there are 4 such pairs which leaves 2 that don't.
%o A397864 (PARI) is_A397864(n) = if(2*sumdiv(n, d, issquare(d + n/d)) > numdiv(n), return(1))
%Y A397864 Cf. A211996, A000005, A005563, A069496, A118593, A232878.
%K A397864 nonn,more,new
%O A397864 1,1
%A A397864 _Žiga Pirc_, Jul 13 2026
